<Heading Size="HeadingSize.Is3">
    Simple Syntax
</Heading>

<BlogPageParagraph>
    In the context of Blazorise, simple syntax without prefixes means that the framework's syntax does not require a prefix before each element, such as <Code>LibButton</Code>, commonly used in other frameworks.
</BlogPageParagraph>

<BlogPageParagraph>
    This syntax approach makes the code more concise, clean, and easy to understand by avoiding unnecessary characters. The Blazorise syntax also allows for easy extension, meaning developers can customize and add their syntax and components to the framework.
</BlogPageParagraph>

